				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's a very small stylistic choice on my part. In a few articles, blue text signifies new text additions, like how strikethrough signifies out-dated text. In this case, the blue text is meant to signal that the date is subject to change or removal.</p> <p>In short: it isn't <em>that</em> important to the article, but I like having it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
